Depends: libc6, libgtk-4-1, libhidapi-hidraw0
Homepage: https://vitalyart.github.io/Aula-F75-Max-Driver/
Description: Native Linux driver for the Aula F75 Max keyboard
 Configure the Epomaker x Aula F75 Max keyboard display, RGB lighting,
 battery status, response level, sleep timeout, Game Mode, and HID diagnostics.
 .
 The app uses Linux hidraw and hidapi directly, installs the required udev
 rule, and keeps wired USB-C display workflows separate from 2.4G receiver
 settings.
 .
 Features include image and GIF upload to the 128 x 128 keyboard display,
 RGB mode controls, battery reading through the 2.4G receiver, performance
 settings, and HID endpoint diagnostics for troubleshooting.
